Given input array of astroid size and its direction <code>(left:positive or right:negative)</code>, find out what will be the result or remaining astroid after their collision.
Example<code>1] Astroid: {-6, 4, 10,}</code>
-6: Astroid of size 6 pound moving in direction right.
4: Astroid of size 4 pound moving in direction left.
-6 will collide with 4 and results in {-6, 10}
-6 collide with 10 and results in {10}
<code>Ans: {10}</code>
Example <code>2] Astroid: {10, -8, 15,}</code>
10 will collide with -8 and results in {10, 15}
<code>Ans: {10,15}</code> as both traveling to left direction.

Algorithm : Keep a stack of remaining asteroids. Going from left to right, if current asteroid has different sign that the last one on the stack, then pop the stack or ignore the variable depending on which has larger absolute value
```
vector<int> collision(vector<int> &a) {
    vector<int> res;
    for (int x:a) {
        while (true) {
            if (res.size() && (res.back() > 0) != (x > 0)) {
                if (abs(x) < abs(res.back())) break;
                if (abs(x) == abs(res.back())) {
                    res.pop_back();
                    break;
                }
                res.pop_back();
            }
            else {
                res.push_back(x);
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    return res;
}
```

```
class Solution:
    def asteroidCollision(self, asteroids: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        stack = []
        i = 0
        curr = asteroids[i]
        while 1:
            if curr > 0:
                stack.append(curr)
                i += 1
                if i == len(asteroids):
                    break
                curr = asteroids[i]
            else:
                if not stack or stack[-1] < 0:
                    stack.append(curr)
                    i += 1
                    if i == len(asteroids):
                        break
                    curr = asteroids[i]
                else:
                    prev = stack.pop()
                    if abs(prev) == abs(curr):
                        i += 1
                        if i == len(asteroids):
                            break
                        curr = asteroids[i]
                    else:
                        curr = curr if abs(curr) > abs(prev) else prev

        return stack
